Author: floatingtales
Content:
Hey so, I kinda want to write about a thinkpiece here about "the true cost of AI" but idk if it is within the topic discussed by gspace.

Things that I might explore on are:
- The environmental costs of AI (Water streams are being used to cool off data centers)
- The privacy costs of AI (Content theft, including art theft, personal data being used to train AI)
- The economic costs of AI (the removal of a lot of junior level employees as they are seen as cost overhead, scams using AI)
- The educational costs of AI (students way too heavily rely on AI to do their work for them, lowering research experience and making them too lazy to learn stuff)

If this is in line with what gspace is discussing, i'll start writing!
